# Frontend Architecture Overview

The frontend is a [Next.js](https://nextjs.org/) application built with TypeScript and React, located in the `frontend/` directory. It uses the App Router paradigm.

## Key Technologies

- **Framework**: [Next.js](https://nextjs.org/) (with App Router)
- **Language**: TypeScript
- **UI Components**: Built with [shadcn/ui](https://ui.shadcn.com/). The base components are in `frontend/components/ui`.
- **Styling**: [Tailwind CSS](https://tailwindcss.com/). Global styles are in `frontend/app/globals.css`.
- **State Management**: The project uses [Zustand](https://github.com/pmndrs/zustand) for state management, as seen in `frontend/package.json`.
- **Markdown Rendering**: It uses `react-markdown` to display markdown content, likely for rendering messages from the AI agent.
- **Linting**: ESLint is configured in `frontend/eslint.config.mjs`.

## Directory Structure

- `frontend/app/`: Contains the application's pages and layouts.
  - `[page.tsx](mdc:frontend/app/page.tsx)`: The main page of the application.
  - `[layout.tsx](mdc:frontend/app/layout.tsx)`: The root layout.
- `frontend/components/`: Reusable React components.
  - `ui/`: Base UI components from shadcn/ui like `[Button](mdc:frontend/components/ui/button.tsx)` and `[Card](mdc:frontend/components/ui/card.tsx)`.
- `frontend/public/`: Static assets like images and SVGs.
- `[package.json](mdc:frontend/package.json)`: Lists all frontend dependencies and scripts.
- `[next.config.ts](mdc:frontend/next.config.ts)`: Next.js configuration.
- `[tsconfig.json](mdc:frontend/tsconfig.json)`: TypeScript configuration.

## Communication with Backend

The frontend is expected to communicate with the `agent_server` backend service, which runs on port 8001 by default. The communication will likely be over HTTP (REST or similar).
